The noise in the hall had abated; 
perhaps Mrs. Weasley and Mundungus had moved 
their argument down into the kitchen.

The walls were bare; 
there were no windows and no doors apart from a 
plain black one set at the very end of the corridor.

Madam Bones looked down at Mrs. Figg in silence; 
Fudge was not looking at her at all, but fidgeting with 
his papers.

His own cauldron 
was issuing copious amounts of dark gray steam; 
Ron’s was spitting green sparks.

His father was a Death Eater, after all; 
what if he had information about Hagrid ’s fate that 
had not yet reached the Order’s ears?

