last couple of wands clattered to the floor.

The Snitch skirted the foot of one of the goal hoops 
and scooted off toward the other side of the stands; 
its change of direction suited Malfoy, who was nearer.

Golgomath’s lot had beaten ’em unconscious; 
they’d woken up an’ crawled inter the nearest shelter 
they could find.

Hermione gasped; 
her mug slipped through her fingers and smashed on 
the floor; Fang yelped.

He returned to the common room half an hour later to 
find Hermione and Ron in the best seats by the fire; 
nearly everybody else had gone to bed.

Harry and Hermione raised their wands; 
now that they had stopped walking, they too could 
hear movement close by.

Auto-Answer Quills are banned 
from the examination hall, as are Remembralls, 
Detachable Cribbing Cuffs, and Self- Correcting Ink.

Hermione gasped, both hands over her mouth; 
Harry looked around at Ron and saw that he too was 
looking scared.

He did not dare attempt to talk to her; 
Umbridge was walking so closely behind them that he 
could hear her ragged breathing.

The chestnut-bodied centaur called 
Magorian was walking toward them out of the circle; 
his bow, like the others’, was raised.

One was bleeding badly; 
Dolohov, freed of the full Body-Bind, was leering, his 
wand pointing straight at Harry’s face.
